    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen using neovim in tmux, and if there are more than two windows such like:\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0b34c174-9763-4fa7-b836-e2420252a25d)\n\nNow If I create a tmux pane (vertical), then close the pane, the layout will look like below (the right most now is half of the screen):\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/271da9bd-e8f2-457c-883d-906e1ea953fd)\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ffea1d4a-e7da-4929-bfb5-da31944c283e)\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. open tmux\n2. open nvim, create three windows\n3. split the tmux vertically\n4. close the new created pane of tmux\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTmux should not affect the layout of neovim.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, vim 9.0\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWSL Ubuntu 24.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwindows termial with tmux 3.2a\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nrepo",
